name: databricks
description: A Pulumi package for creating and managing Databricks cloud resources.
attribution: This Pulumi package is based on the [`databricks` Terraform Provider](https://github.com/terraform-providers/terraform-provider-databricks).

azurePatTokenDurationSeconds.description: Currently secret scopes are not accessible via AAD tokens so we will need to create a PAT token

azureUsePatForCli.description: Create ephemeral PAT tokens also for AZ CLI authenticated requests

azureUsePatForSpn.description: Create ephemeral PAT tokens instead of AAD tokens for SPN

configFile.description:
Location of the Databricks CLI credentials file, that is created by `databricks configure --token` command. By default,
it is located in ~/.databrickscfg. Check https://docs.databricks.com/dev-tools/cli/index.html#set-up-authentication for
docs. Config file credentials will only be used when host/token are not provided.

debugHeaders.description: Debug HTTP headers of requests made by the provider. Default is false. Visible only when TF_LOG=DEBUG is set

debugTruncateBytes.description: Truncate JSON fields in JSON above this limit. Default is 96. Visible only when TF_LOG=DEBUG is set

profile.description:
Connection profile specified within ~/.databrickscfg. Please check
https://docs.databricks.com/dev-tools/cli/index.html#connection-profiles for documentation.

rateLimit.description: Maximum number of requests per second made to Databricks REST API by Terraform.

skipVerify.description: Skip SSL certificate verification for HTTP calls. Use at your own risk.

provider.description:
The provider type for the databricks package. By default, resources use package-wide configuration
settings, however an explicit `Provider` instance may be created and passed during resource
construction to achieve fine-grained programmatic control over provider settings. See the
[documentation](https://www.pulumi.com/docs/reference/programming-model/#providers) for more information.
